      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must hold ISO 9001 certification or equivalent SQA documentation covering version control, regression testing, and release validation.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is deployed under a documented SQA plan that includes automated regression suites, version-controlled input decks, and signed release notes. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2 for MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through published benchmark problems (e.g., lid-driven cavity, Poiseuille flow) at the order of accuracy expected from the discretisation scheme.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent code verification is documented in published literature and vendor verification reports covering second-order spatial accuracy on structured and unstructured meshes. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for the primary QoI (normalised hemolysis index) across at least three systematically refined meshes, with GCI < 5% on the fine mesh.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (4.2 M, 9.8 M, and 21.4 M cells) was conducted at the 6 L/min / 2400 rpm operating point. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI = 2.1% on the fine mesh, satisfying the criterion. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid temperature, viscosity, inlet flow waveform) must be documented and reproduced in the simulation boundary conditions within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments used a glycerol-water blood analogue at 37 °C with viscosity 3.5 cP. Simulation boundary conditions replicate these values within 2%. Temperature and fluid properties are matched. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalised hemolysis index and velocity field must agree with experimental measurements within two experimental standard deviations across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD predictions of the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) fall within 1.4 experimental standard deviations at all five operating points. PIV velocity comparisons show mean relative error of 7.3% in the blade-passage region. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, RH) must directly map to the decision criterion (RH < 1) without untested transformations.",
      "rationale": "NIH is computed directly from the power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle paths. RH is derived as the ratio of device NIH to predicate NIH using identical post-processing. No untested transformations are introduced. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry (or a qualified surrogate) and span the operating envelope of the COU, including the extended paediatric flow range introduced at MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments cover the FDA generic pump across 3–7 L/min and 2000–3500 rpm, encompassing the adult CPB operating envelope. The paediatric extension (1–3 L/min) is partially outside the validated range; however, interpolation uncertainty is bounded by sensitivity analysis. Required level 2 met with noted limitation on paediatric extrapolation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated by residual reduction of at least four orders of magnitude and stability of the primary QoI monitor over the final 500 iterations.",
      "rationale": "All five operating-point simulations achieve continuity residuals below 1×10⁻⁵ and NIH monitor variation below 0.3% over the final 500 iterations. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup must be independently reviewed by a second qualified analyst against a documented checklist covering mesh, boundary conditions, solver settings, and post-processing scripts.",
      "rationale": "An independent senior CFD engineer reviewed the complete simulation setup against the internal checklist (form QA-CFD-007). Two minor boundary-condition discrepancies were identified and corrected prior to production runs. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence closure and hemolysis power-law model must be justified by literature evidence for rotating blood-contacting devices, and sensitivity to model-form choices must be reported.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model is selected based on published comparisons for centrifugal pumps. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the regulatory standard for CFD hemolysis prediction. Sensitivity to turbulence model (k-ε vs SST k-ω) shows NIH variation of ±8%, reported in the credibility evidence package. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, rotational speed, flow rates) must be traceable to calibrated measurements or manufacturer specifications with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry is derived from FDA-released CAD files (tolerance ±0.01 mm). Fluid properties are taken from ASTM F1841 with stated uncertainty. Rotational speeds are set to ±10 rpm of nominal. Traceability matrix provided in Appendix B of the credibility report. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples used for validation must be characterised for dimensional conformance to the nominal geometry, and any deviations must be quantified and propagated to the QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three physical pump specimens were measured by CMM; maximum dimensional deviation from nominal is 0.04 mm, producing a NIH sensitivity of <1.5% based on adjoint-based shape sensitivity analysis. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters used during validation must be demonstrated to be equivalent to those applicable in the COU, including any patient-specific or device-specific variations not present in the validation dataset.",
      "rationale": "The validation experiments were conducted using the FDA generic pump geometry, which is nominally identical to the device geometry evaluated in this COU. Because the geometry is the same physical design, it was determined during planning that a formal equivalency assessment of input parameters does not apply to this COU—the validation conditions are considered inherently representative. No separate equivalency analysis was therefore performed. This reasoning conflates geometric identity with full input-parameter equivalency; in particular, blood rheology variability across the paediatric patient population, device-specific manufacturing tolerances at the upper bound of the tolerance stack, and the extended low-flow paediatric operating regime were not formally compared against the validation dataset inputs. The factor has consequently been left not-assessed rather than formally scoped out or classified as not-applicable."
    }
  ],
